{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-project-js","path":"/projects/trm","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"6ff11fb2-cae9-572d-afd5-0a8467ca51f0","html":"<p>TRM (Tiny Ray Marcher) is a C++ project that implement a very small ray\nmarching algorithm. The project implements the fundamental components of a path\ntracer, and even provides an easy to use scene definition file.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 650px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/5d52e53aabbf538ebad5b5ad1a59b3c9/e8950/trm1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Meneger Sponge\"\n        title=\"Meneger Sponge\"\n        src=\"/static/5d52e53aabbf538ebad5b5ad1a59b3c9/a6d36/trm1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/5d52e53aabbf538ebad5b5ad1a59b3c9/222b7/trm1.png 163w,\n/static/5d52e53aabbf538ebad5b5ad1a59b3c9/ff46a/trm1.png 325w,\n/static/5d52e53aabbf538ebad5b5ad1a59b3c9/a6d36/trm1.png 650w,\n/static/5d52e53aabbf538ebad5b5ad1a59b3c9/e548f/trm1.png 975w,\n/static/5d52e53aabbf538ebad5b5ad1a59b3c9/3c492/trm1.png 1300w,\n/static/5d52e53aabbf538ebad5b5ad1a59b3c9/e8950/trm1.png 2000w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h4 id=\"efficiency\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#efficiency\" aria-label=\"efficiency permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Efficiency</h4>\n<p>By changing specific key configuration values in a rendered image, it is\npossible to significantly alter the quality of the image, in direct relation to\nthe runtime of the program. However some settings will produce a better output\nimage, for less cost to runtime. The main two settings that we consider here,\nis the <strong>spp</strong> and the <strong>resolution</strong>. By doubling the spp it can be considered\nthat we are rendering twice as many images, and combining the images after the\nfact. While doubling the resolution is equivalent to rendering four times the\nnumber of images, and connecting the images as the four quadrants of the output\nimage.</p>\n<p>After collecting the data it is clear that doubling the resolution in both axis\nis indeed about equivalent to four times the samples per pixel. However,\nincreasing the resolution produces a visually shaper images, even with very few\nsamples.</p>\n<div class=\"custom-block note\"><div class=\"custom-block-body\"><p>More quantitative data is still being determined.</p></div></div>\n<h4 id=\"configuration\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#configuration\" aria-label=\"configuration permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Configuration</h4>\n<p>The scene file is based upon JSON file format. The general file is formatted\nlike so:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"cpp\"><pre class=\"language-cpp\"><code class=\"language-cpp\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token string\">\"spp\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">128</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token string\">\"maxiumumDepth\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">64</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token string\">\"resolution\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">2000</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">2000</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token string\">\"camera\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token string\">\"fov\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">1.5707</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token string\">\"center\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">0.0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">0.0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">0.0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token string\">\"up\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">0.0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">1.0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">0.0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token string\">\"pos\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">0.0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">0.0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token number\">6.0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token string\">\"materials\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token string\">\"objects\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h5 id=\"general\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#general\" aria-label=\"general permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>General</h5>\n<p>These are general settings for the render, they control how the renderer will\nfunction, and the quality of the produced image. Changing these values will\nsignificantly impact the runtime of the renderer. The amount that each value\neffects the runtime is described in the section on <a href=\"#efficiency\">Efficiency</a>.</p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Value</th>\n<th>Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><code class=\"language-text\">spp</code></td>\n<td>The number of samples per pixel. Higher values will result in better looking images.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code class=\"language-text\">maxiumumDepth</code></td>\n<td>The number of bounces that the simulation will simulate before rays begin to terminate.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code class=\"language-text\">resolution</code></td>\n<td>The width and height of the output image.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code class=\"language-text\">camera</code></td>\n<td>Information about the camera object in the scene.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code class=\"language-text\">camera.fov</code></td>\n<td>The field of view for the camera given in radians.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code class=\"language-text\">camera.center</code></td>\n<td>The point in the scene that the camera will be focused at.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code class=\"language-text\">camera.up</code></td>\n<td>The direction that will be the up direction relative to the camera.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code class=\"language-text\">camera.pos</code></td>\n<td>The position of the camera object in the scene.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h5 id=\"materials\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#materials\" aria-label=\"materials permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Materials</h5>","timeToRead":2,"frontmatter":{"date":"March 06, 2020","path":"/projects/trm","title":"TRM","tags":["c++","graphics"],"github":"https://github.com/LuxAter/trm"}}},"pageContext":{}}}